  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "When running `hardhat node`, it exposes itself as \"chainId 31337\", but the assembly OPCODE `chainid` returns value \"1\"\r\n\r\nAny code that uses EIP712 validates the chainId in a contract, and thus all signature checks are broken.\r\n\r\nThis is probably related to the same [bug in ganache](https://github.com/trufflesuite/ganache-core/issues/515) (though in ganache, it was already fixed, so that when specifying `--chainId xxx`, the same value will get returned by both RPC call and opcode `chainid`)\r\n\r\n(Note that back then in ganache I could workaround by adding \"--chainId 1\", but with hardhat, I can't pass this option, so we can't use it)",
